gomodel:SYNGO_5553  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 4: VPS26B knockout cultured neurons show a decrease of surface GluA1 by western blot (A) and imaging (C) without affecting total levels of GluA1. In the VPS26B knockout, the GluA1 receptor accumulates in possynaptic early and recycling endosomes (B). The surface levels of GluA1 can be restored by reexpression of VPS26B-GFP.\n\nFig 3B: VPS26B knockout mice show impaired LTP in the trans-entorhinal cortex (TEC).\nFig 5F: AAV9-VPS26b-GFP expression in the TEC can restore LTP in VPS26B knockout mice. Experimental description: p-Lenti-C-mGFP VPS26b OriGene Technologies, Inc. Cat#MR204988L4\nForm OriGene: Lenti ORF clone of Vps26b (mGFP-tagged) - Mouse vacuolar protein sorting 26 homolog B (yeast) (Vps26b)\n\nRabbit polyclonal anti-GluA1 C-terminus MilliporeSigma Cat#AB1504; RRID: AB_2113602\nRabbit polyclonal anti-VPS26b Novus Biologicals Cat#NBP1-92575\nRabbit polyclonal anti-Syntaxin13 Synaptic Systems Cat#110 133;\nGoat polyclonal anti-EEA1 Santa Cruz Biotechnology, Inc. Cat#sc-6415;" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5553" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

